Durban - The only suspect arrested for the murder of Avoca father Kelly Chetty made a brief appearance in the Durban Regional Court on Thursday. Sphamandla Buthelezi, 32, of KwaMashu, was remanded in custody and will make his next appearance in September. Buthelezi faces murder and attempted hijacking charges. On May 31, Chetty, who was with his two children, had parked at the side of the road to buy vegetables at uMhlangane Road, when he was accosted by four armed men who demanded the keys to his red VW Golf R. According to police Chetty had refused to hand over the keys and was shot. The following day two men believed to have been linked to Chetty's hijacking was killed by police during a shoot-out in KwaMashu. Buthelezi was arrested after he sought medical help at the Poly Clinic in KwaMashu after the shooting incident. He spent time in a hospital, but has recovered and is now an awaiting trial prisoner at Westville Prison. The case has been remanded for further investigation. According to a source close to the investigation, the DNA and the ballistics reports were still not ready. Daily News 